[SN]TITLE[SN]
Swansea City praised for Liberty Stadium disabled provisions

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Swansea City football club has been praised for the number of spaces it provides for wheelchair users.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
According to disability charity Revitalise, they have room for 179 home fans and 12 in the away end.
Along with Arsenal and AFC Bournemouth, they are one of only three Premier League teams to provide the 150 spaces suggested in national guidelines.
Swansea's Liberty Stadium finished fifth overall in Revitalise's table of fan satisfaction over accessibility.
Disabled supporters association members from all 20 Premier League sides gave their views.
Revitalise gave Swansea City an overall satisfaction rating of 79%. Issues like stewarding, seating, views of the action, match day experience and feelings of exclusion were used to determine this.
